name: WorldEvent.Unload
description: WorldEvent.Unload is fired when Minecraft unloads a world. This event is fired when a world is unloaded in Minecraft.setLevel(ClientLevel) , MinecraftServer.stopServer() ,, Minecraft.clearLevel(Screen) ForgeInternalHandler.onDimensionUnload(Unload) . This event is not Cancelable . This event does not have a result. Event.HasResult This event is fired on the MinecraftForge.EVENT_BUS .
